<strong>Verify Screen Functionality</strong>
Case ID: his-001

This tests that ubuntu works with a built-in screen
<dl>
    <dt>Boot the computer</dt>
        <dd>The login screen should load normally</dd>
    <dt>Log into the computer</dt>
        <dd>The desktop wallpaper and panels should be displayed as normal</dd>
    <dt>Open the settings manager, then open the display settings (might be call "monitor" or "display")</dt>
    <dt>Change the screen resolution by selecting a different resolution from the Resolution dropdown list.</dt>
    <dt>Press 'Apply'. Verify that the new resolution is set correctly and that the screen is still visible. </dt>
        <dd>The new resolution isset correctly and the screen is still visible</dd>
</dl>

